main event: Two unidentified flying objects were observed in Trenton, Michigan on January 25, 1964, with conflicting details about their sightings.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for 35 minutes, The objects were reported to move from northwest to southeast and then southwest, There were conflicting reports on their speed and trajectory, The observer noted variable speeds and difficulty in tracking the objects, A hand-drawn sketch of a saucer-shaped object was included in the report.
witness description: 19-year-old male who reported seeing the object and noted high speeds.
